"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Remove Stored Transcript Path from Checkpoint Metadata\n\n## Context\n\nWhen running `entire resume`, the CLI restores session transcripts from checkpoints. Currently, checkpoint metadata stores a `transcript_path` field that embeds the original repository location, causing restoration to fail when the project moves.\n\n## The Problem\n\nAgents (Claude Code, Gemini CLI) store transcripts in directories derived from the repository path:\n- Claude: `~/.claude/projects/-Users-alice-projects-cli/session.jsonl`\n- Gemini: `~/.gemini/tmp/-Users-alice-projects-cli/chats/session.json`\n\nThe \"project directory\" component (`-Users-alice-projects-cli`) is created by sanitizing the repo absolute path (`/Users/alice/projects/cli`), replacing non-alphanumeric characters with dashes.\n\n**When a project moves:**\n1. Checkpoint created on machine A: `/Users/alice/projects/cli`\n2. Transcript stored at: `~/.claude/projects/-Users-alice-projects-cli/session.jsonl`\n3. Checkpoint metadata saves: `.claude/projects/-Users-alice-projects-cli/session.jsonl`\n4. Project cloned on machine B: `/Users/bob/work/cli`\n5. Agent now stores transcripts at: `~/.claude/projects/-Users-bob-work-cli/session.jsonl`\n6. Resume tries to restore to: `~/.claude/projects/-Users-alice-projects-cli/session.jsonl` (WRONG!)\n\nThis breaks cross-machine portability and even moving repos on the same machine.\n\n## Root Cause Analysis\n\n**Two different TranscriptPath fields:**\n\n1. **`session.State.TranscriptPath`** (runtime session state in `.git/entire-sessions/`):\n   - Points to the **live transcript file** during an active session\n   - Used for mid-session commit detection (when user commits before calling `Stop`)\n   - Updated on each turn from the agent's hook input\n   - **This one IS needed** - operational data for tracking active sessions\n\n2. **`CommittedMetadata.TranscriptPath`** (checkpoint metadata on `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch):\n   - Stored as home-relative path (e.g., `.claude/projects/-Users-alice-projects-cli/`)\n   - Intended for resume to restore transcript to original location\n   - **This one causes the bug** - embeds the sanitized repo path from checkpoint creation time\n\n**The stored path is unnecessary because:**\n- We can always compute the correct transcript path from the current repo location using `agent.GetSessionDir(repoRoot)`\n- The computed path automatically handles repo moves/clones\n- Even agents with \"complex\" path schemes (like Gemini's hashing) still derive paths from the repo location, so they have the same problem\n\n## Solution\n\n**Stop storing `transcript_path` in checkpoint metadata entirely.** Always compute the transcript path at restore time based on the current repo location.\n\n### Implementation\n\n1. **Remove `SessionTranscriptPath` from checkpoint writes** (`manual_commit_condensation.go`)\n   - Delete line that sets `SessionTranscriptPath: homeRelativePath(state.TranscriptPath)`\n   - This stops writing the field to new checkpoints\n\n2. **Update `RestoreLogsOnly()` to always compute transcript path** (`manual_commit_rewind.go`)\n   - Remove `resolveTranscriptPathFromMetadata()` call\n   - Always use `agent.GetSessionDir(repoRoot)` to compute session directory from current repo location\n   - Use `ResolveSessionFilePath()` to construct the full transcript path\n   - This makes restoration location-independent\n\n3. **Keep struct fields for backward compatibility**\n   - Keep `CommittedMetadata.TranscriptPath` field and JSON tag (old checkpoints may have it)\n   - Keep `WriteCommittedOptions.SessionTranscriptPath` field (not used anymore but avoids breaking API)\n   - Mark as deprecated in comments\n\n4. **Update auto-commit strategy similarly**\n   - Remove `TranscriptPath` writes in auto-commit condensation\n   - Update any restoration logic if needed\n\n### Why This Works\n\n- **Always uses current repo location**: `agent.GetSessionDir(repoRoot)` computes where the agent stores transcripts based on the CURRENT repo path\n- **Handles all repo moves**: Whether the repo moves on the same machine or is cloned to a different machine\n- **Simpler logic**: No fallback path resolution, no special cases\n- **Backward compatible**: Old checkpoints with `transcript_path` are ignored (we just compute the correct path anyway)\n\n## Critical Files to Modify\n\n1. **`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`** (line ~237)\n   - Remove: `SessionTranscriptPath: homeRelativePath(state.TranscriptPath),`\n   - This stops writing transcript path to new checkpoints\n\n2. **`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go`** (lines 707-719)\n   - Replace stored path resolution with computed path resolution\n   - Always call `agent.GetSessionDir(repoRoot)` → `ResolveSessionFilePath()`\n   - Remove `resolveTranscriptPathFromMetadata()` call\n\n3. **`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/auto_commit.go`** (check for similar usage)\n   - Search for any `SessionTranscriptPath` or `TranscriptPath` writes\n   - Remove if present\n\n4. **Add deprecation comments** to struct fields:\n   - `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/checkpoint.go` - `CommittedMetadata.TranscriptPath`\n   - `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/checkpoint.go` - `WriteCommittedOptions.SessionTranscriptPath`\n\n## Related Files (Reference Only - No Changes)\n\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/claude.go:162-175` - Claude's GetSessionDir (computes path from repo location)\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/gemini.go:187-201` - Gemini's GetSessionDir (same pattern)\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go:244-257` - `homeRelativePath()` helper (can remain, might be used elsewhere)\n- `cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go:125-126` - Runtime `State.TranscriptPath` (keep as-is, different purpose)\n\n## Verification\n\n### Manual Testing\n\n1. **Test scenario 1**: Resume in moved repo\n   - Create checkpoint in `/tmp/test-repo`\n   - Move repo to `/tmp/different-location/test-repo`\n   - Run `entire resume` - should restore